Recording.Name: Inventory adjustment with inventory journal posting

Annotation.Description: Company = USMF One unit of the Speaker Cable (item T0001) with the size 10 has been previously reported as damaged in the warehouse 21 at site 2 and took out from the regular inventory. The unit was physically put in a quarantine location, sitting there for some times until John notices it. It turns out that it was a misclassification and the unit is in the normal state so Ellen, the warehouse manager, proceeds to a positive inventory adjustment to correct the user error and physically moves the unit back into the regular inventory.
Annotation.Title: Read the note. Then go to Inventory management > Journals > Item transactions > Inventory adjustment.

In the Description field, enter 'Inventory adjustment - damage correction'
